channel.title: Advanced winterLove programmers wanted in here! [Team Alpha]
channel.description:
I'm going to keep this brief. This is not for a specific server. I do not want kids in here who have 6 posts and think programming is inserting a custom command I'm looking for a few members of this forum to develop some winterLove fixes with so that we can help to fix up some servers and release the content as tutorials. We would be doing stuff such as updating the old login block and creating tutorials for regional updating for NPC's and players. I'm inserting a basic application just so that I can filter out any kids. Clawz, I'm looking at you to join this team! Application:
Name: Years working with winterLove: Skype:
Current content development team -Christmas_tree -Clawz fury -Arham 4 -The elve age - EDIT: are you kidding me? I was certain I put this in the team section... Can somebody move the topic please?

omfg, the elve age? this is starting to get me excited
[/quote]I’m not that java-smart, so don’t be haha.[/quote]

I know that you’ll be able to help out with many things! The community still lacks a tutorial or explanation on how player clipping and NPC clipping work, so I’m sure you’ll be a very useful addition to the team! Even if it means you only explain the code and don’t write that much, your help is always wanted! Thanks for joining the team!

We still have slots for one or two more programmers, otherwise development for global material will begin later this week. All current members have been added on Skype and I hope to talk to all of you soon. Checking at 7:00 gmt I was still missing an accept from elve and Arham, but I’m sure they’ve accepted by now.
